  "pr_description": "## Summary\n\n`stacc submit` had two bugs in PR description handling.\n\n**Bug 1: Hard-wrapped commit bodies rendered with mid-sentence line breaks on GitHub.**\n`commit_body()` returns raw git output with conventional 72-column hard wraps. GitHub GFM renders each bare newline as `<br>`, breaking sentences in the middle of words. Fix: `reflow_body()` helper joins lines within blank-line-separated paragraphs before using commit body as PR description.\n\n**Bug 2: Re-submit always overwrote manually-edited PR body.**\n`PullRequestUpdate` always sent `body: Some(body)` on every PATCH, silently overwriting edits made via `gh pr edit`. The struct already had `body: Option<String>` with `skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\"`. Fix: introduce `update_body: Option<String>` that is `None` when no explicit description source exists (no `--description` flag and no previously-stored description), causing the PATCH to omit the field and GitHub to preserve its current value.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- `reflow_body(text: &str) -> String`: private helper in `commands.rs`. Single-pass String write; splits on blank lines, joins paragraph lines with space, rejoins paragraphs with `\\n\\n`. Applied only at `commit_body()` fallback call sites.\n- `update_body: Option<String>`: computed after the body cascade. `Some(desc)` only when `--description` was passed on this run or a stored description exists. `None` otherwise.\n- `PullRequestUpdate.body: update_body` — relies on the existing `skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\"` to omit the field from PATCH JSON.\n\n## Testing\n\n- 4 new integration tests in `crates/stacc/tests/submit.rs`: single wrapped paragraph reflowed on CREATE, multi-paragraph reflowed on CREATE, `--description` bypasses reflow, PATCH omits body field when no explicit source (exact-body httpmock matcher).\n- 7 new unit tests for `reflow_body` edge cases (empty, single-line, trailing newlines, multi-blank-line collapse, trailing whitespace).\n- 2 new unit tests in `stacc-github/src/lib.rs` pinning `PullRequestUpdate` serialization: body absent from JSON when `None`, body present when `Some`.\n- All 617 workspace tests pass.\n\n## Known Residuals\n\nThese advisory findings from code review are accepted and deferred:\n\n- **F2 (P2/advisory):** `reflow_body` silently mangles structured markdown (list items, block-quotes) in commit bodies when not separated by blank lines. Explicitly deferred per plan scope boundaries. Doc comment notes plain-prose-only intent.\n- **F3 (P2/advisory):** Commit body amendments after first `stacc submit` (no `--description`, no `stored_desc`) are not reflected in subsequent PATCH calls. Design trade-off per R4/R5: PATCH omits body when no explicit source to preserve manual edits. Use `--description` to update PR body after amending a commit.\n- **F4 (P2/advisory):** `--description \"\"` stores `Some(\"\")` and permanently sends `body:\"\"` (clearing the GitHub PR body) on every future re-submit. Undocumented but arguably correct. No test.\n- **F8 (P3/advisory):** AGENTS.md missing: `--description` flag, `@path` syntax, description priority chain, `adopted` field, reflow behavior documentation.\n- **F9 (P3/advisory):** `commands.rs` now >1000 lines; `reflow_body` belongs in a text utility module.\n\n## Post-Deploy Monitoring & Validation\n\nNo additional operational monitoring required. This is a local CLI change with no server-side component. Validation: run `stacc submit` on a branch whose commit body has conventional 72-column wrapping and verify the resulting GitHub PR description shows joined sentences. Run `gh pr edit` to set a custom body, then `stacc submit` again, and verify the custom body is preserved.\n"
